narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: knowledge about plays that are part of the American theater cannon that I would otherwise not have had the opportunity to read (it's not often that these types of plays are at the front of the bookstore!)

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
strength: discussion
weakness: finishing whole plays for each class meeting (including ones during the weeks a paper was due) made it so that inevitably I had at least a couple of class meetings where I hadn't read enough to feel engaged in the discussion

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes! It was engaging, and intellectually stimulating to be able to learn about the cannon of American drama that can further inform your current understandings of today's theater. If you're interested in studying or performing theater, or even just seeing the occasional show every now and then, this course helps to give you a more holistic lens to view it through.

narratives.question_text: The Canvas course site allowed me to identify and access required course materials easily.
